article.headline: Indiana State 73, Bradley 63
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- David Moss had 16 points, eight boards and five assists Saturday to lead Indiana State over Bradley, 73-63. Gabriel Moore tied his career high with 16 points as the Sycamores (8-13, 3-7) snapped a six-game losing streak. Amani Daanish added 14 points and six rebounds for ISU in the Missouri Valley Conference matchup. Tony Bennett shot 8-of-17 to score a game-high 20 points to lead the Braves (11-7, 4-6). The Sycamores led throughout and outshot the Braves 52.3 percent to 43.3 percent. Both teams committed almost the same number of turnovers, Bradley had 13 and ISU had 14, but ISU gave up only 13 points off turnovers, while Bradley gave up 25. Marcellus Sommerville was the only other Brave to score in double digits with 15 points, 14 of them in the second half. He also had five rebounds, while Daniel Ruffin added nine points, four rebounds and four assists for Bradley.
